      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## Memory Retrieval Tracking\n\n**SessionStart Hook Activity** (captured in activity log, not Prometheus due to one-off process limitation):\n\n```bash\n# View recent memory retrievals\ntail -50 ~/.bmad-memory/logs/activity.log | grep RETRIEVAL\n\n# Count retrievals by project (last 100 lines)\ntail -100 ~/.bmad-memory/logs/activity.log | grep RETRIEVAL | grep -oP 'project=[^ ]+' | sort | uniq -c\n\n# View retrieval timing stats\ntail -100 ~/.bmad-memory/logs/activity.log | grep RETRIEVAL | grep -oP 'duration_ms=[0-9]+' | cut -d= -f2 | awk '{sum+=$1; count++} END {print \"Avg: \"sum/count\"ms, Total: \"count\" retrievals\"}'\n```\n\n**What This Proves:**\n- **Capture:** Embeddings/min shows memories being created âœ…\n- **Storage:** Collection growth proves persistent storage âœ…  \n- **Retrieval:** Activity log tracks SessionStart context injection âœ…\n- **Token Savings:** Estimated 1500-2500 tokens saved per session with memory retrieval âœ…\n\n**Future Enhancement (Story 6.7):** Prometheus Pushgateway will enable retrieval metrics in this dashboard."
      }
